 book explore how the term theopoetics contributes to cutting-edge work in theology, philosophy, literature, and sociology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Religious.2bisacsh1 aCaputo, John D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColapietro, Vincent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFaber, Roland, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFaber, Roland, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFackenthal, Jeremy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFackenthal, Jeremy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFiddes, Paul S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalewood, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHiggins, Luke B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeefe-Perry, L. Callid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeller, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaurent, Sam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLopresti, Matthew S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMesle, C. Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhelps, Hollis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchneider, Laurel C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThatamanil, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831107072980 cprintz978082325156840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082329333940uhttps://ww